medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute onset of lower abdominal pain.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The pain started at 2pm yesterday. It was suprapubic, crampy, non-radiating, and worse with movement. Since the pain began, the patient has not wanted to eat, experienced nausea, and had 2 episodes of nonbloody/non-bilious emesis. There was no diarrhea, fever, or chills.
